      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's completely understandable to feel that way when the \"new chapter\" narrative feels like a hollow lie. When the core of who you were seems to have vanished, keeping the rest of the life going can feel like maintaining a lifeless shell. It's not about finding a new purpose right now; it's about acknowledging that the old version of you is gone and that the current version, however empty or hollow it feels, is all that remains. You don't have to force it to feel new or meaningful just yet.",
      "source": "target",
